doctype html
html
    head
        title  YCP Hacks
        // CSS only
        meta(name='viewport', content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1')
        link(rel='icon', type='image/x-icon', href='/static/images/favicon.png')
        link(rel='stylesheet', type='text/css', href='/static/stylesheets/welcomePage.css')

    body
        .margin.m-2
            h1.display-5.my-5 What is Hackathon?
            .container.shadow.text-center
                p#intro.fs-5.p-3
                    | Conveniently nestled in the middle of rural Pennsylvania, YCP Hacks is a
                    | college level hackathon with small town charm. An hour north of Baltimore, an hour and a
                    | half from Philadelphia, and 2 hours from Penn State places it right in the middle of
                    | Pennsylvania Dutch Country (presumably made of funnel cake). The event is set on the
                    | charming York College of Pennsylvania campus, with all the facilities, people and
                    | camaraderie that comes with it. Our mission is to promote technical knowledge,
                    | innovation, and entrepreneurship in York and beyond, and we just can't wait to see
                    | what you do next.

            h1.display-5.my-5 Schedule
            .container.p-3.shadow
                ul#myTab.nav.nav-tabs.nav-justified(role='tablist')
                    li.nav-item(role='presentation')
                        button#home-tab.nav-link.link-dark.active(data-bs-toggle='tab', data-bs-target='#home-tab-pane', type='button', role='tab', aria-controls='home-tab-pane', aria-selected='true') Friday
                    li.nav-item(role='presentation')
                        button#profile-tab.nav-link.link-dark(data-bs-toggle='tab', data-bs-target='#profile-tab-pane', type='button', role='tab', aria-controls='profile-tab-pane', aria-selected='false') Saturday
                    li.nav-item(role='presentation')
                        button#contact-tab.nav-link.link-dark(data-bs-toggle='tab', data-bs-target='#contact-tab-pane', type='button', role='tab', aria-controls='contact-tab-pane', aria-selected='false') Sunday
                #myTabContent.tab-content
                    #home-tab-pane.tab-pane.fade.show.active(role='tabpanel', aria-labelledby='home-tab', tabindex='0')

                        table.table.table-striped
                            thead
                                tr
                                    th(scope='col') Event
                                    th(scope='col') Time
                                    th(scope='col') Location
                            tbody
                                each item of data
                                    tr
                                        each value of item
                                            td(style="width: 5px;")=value
                    #profile-tab-pane.tab-pane.fade(role='tabpanel', aria-labelledby='profile-tab', tabindex='0') ...
                    #contact-tab-pane.tab-pane.fade(role='tabpanel', aria-labelledby='contact-tab', tabindex='0') ...
            // END OF SCHEDULE

            h1.display-5.my-5 FAQ
            div(style='text-align: center; padding-bottom: 50px;')
                button.FAQ.accordion What&apos;s a Hackathon?
                .panel
                    p
                        | A 36 hour event where you work together with a team to make something awesome. You don&apos;t need to know
                        | how to code or be a supreme hacker, just how to be creative! You can also get help from our mentors
                        | and speakers who will be attending.
                button.FAQ.accordion Can I come?
                .panel
                    p
                        | We&apos;ll take any college student from anywhere on earth! We sadly cannot accept students under the age
                        | of 18. All students from outside of York College may be asked to attend online if Covid protocols
                        | change
                button.FAQ.accordion Where is this going to be?
                .panel
                    p
                        | The Willman Business Center of York College! There will be free parking in the adjacent lot for the
                        | entire weekend.
                button.FAQ.accordion When will this be?
                .panel
                    p
                        | November 4-6, 2022
                button.FAQ.accordion Why?
                .panel
                    p
                        | Learn new things, meet new people, and tons of free food and swag.
                button.FAQ.accordion Will you reimburse travel?
                .panel
                    p
                        | If we get enough sponsors this season, we may offer it closer to the event date. At this time we
                        | cannot confirm it though. Apply and we&apos;ll email our applicants with more information as it becomes
                        | available.
                button.FAQ.accordion But I can&apos;t code!
                .panel
                    P
                        | We&apos;ll have tons of great workshops and mentors to help you learn and build something amazing!
                button.FAQ.accordion How much does it cost?
                .panel
                    p
                        | Nothing! Registration is free and food will be provided for you. And of course, swag is free too.
                button.FAQ.accordion Will there be hardware available?
                .panel
                    p
                        | Yes! Hardware will be provided.
                button.FAQ.accordion What should I bring?
                .panel
                    p
                        | ID, Clothing, sleeping bag, and any necessary tech (and chargers). And deodorant. Please.
                button.FAQ.accordion Do I keep my Intellectual Property?
                .panel
                    p
                        | Yes! Participants retain 100% of the intellectual property that they create during the event.
                button.FAQ.accordion Are there any rules?
                .panel
                    p
                        | You can find the MLH code here: https://static.mlh.io/docs/mlh-code-of-conduct.pdf&quot
                button.FAQ.accordion You didn&apos;t answer my question!
                .panel
                    p
                        | Send it to us at info@ycphacks.io!
            script.
                var acc = document.getElementsByClassName("accordion");
                var i;
                for (i = 0; i < acc.length; i++) {
                    acc[i].addEventListener("click", function () {
                        this.classList.toggle("active");
                        var panel = this.nextElementSibling;
                        if (panel.style.maxHeight) {
                            panel.style.maxHeight = null;
                        } else {
                            panel.style.maxHeight = panel.scrollHeight + "px";
                        }
                    });
                }

